From: race-detector-experiments
Subject: [experimental] Make AITER importable on a non-ROCm machine

AITER is ROCm-only by design. Three module-load-time barriers stop it from
even being `import aiter`-able on a CUDA box:

  1. setup.py:148 raises if BUILD_TARGET != "rocm".
     (We don't pip-install AITER, so this only matters for the optional
     install fallback. Patched anyway.)
  2. aiter/jit/utils/cpp_extension.py:169 calls get_hip_version() at module
     load — raises "ROCm version file not found" on CUDA.
  3. aiter/__init__.py imports `from .utility import dtypes` *inside* the
     CK/HIP try block. That try block aborts on `from .jit import core`,
     so `aiter.dtypes` never gets exposed even though dtypes.py itself only
     needs torch + a GFX string.

This patch does the minimum to clear all three. Subsequent ROCm assumptions
deeper in AITER are NOT addressed — many tests will still fail to collect
on CUDA. This is local-only experimental scaffolding, not an upstream-
supported AITER CUDA build.

Apply with:
    cd aiter && git apply ../patches/aiter-cuda-experimental.patch

Pair with environment variable:
    export GPU_ARCHS=gfx942
so chip_info.get_gfx() short-circuits past rocminfo.

This patch is NOT meant to be committed into the aiter submodule.

--- a/setup.py
+++ b/setup.py
@@ -145,8 +145,9 @@ if not _is_metadata_only() and not IS_WINDOWS:
     else:
         IS_ROCM = False

-    if not IS_ROCM:
-        raise NotImplementedError("Only ROCM is supported")
+    if not IS_ROCM:
+        print("[experimental] Non-ROCm build: skipping CK/HIP extension build", flush=True)
+        ENABLE_CK = False

     ck_dir = os.environ.get("CK_DIR", f"{this_dir}/3rdparty/composable_kernel")
     if ENABLE_CK:
--- a/aiter/jit/utils/cpp_extension.py
+++ b/aiter/jit/utils/cpp_extension.py
@@ -89,7 +89,8 @@ def get_hip_version():
         hipconfig = executable_path("hipconfig")
         output = subprocess.check_output([hipconfig, "--version"], text=True)
         return output
     except Exception:
-        raise RuntimeError("ROCm version file not found")
+        # On non-ROCm hosts return None so module load completes; downstream
+        # code branches on IS_HIP_EXTENSION which falls back to False.
+        return None
--- a/aiter/__init__.py
+++ b/aiter/__init__.py
@@ -65,12 +65,14 @@ if os.path.isdir(_flydsl_cache) and "FLYDSL_RUNTIME_CACHE_DIR" not in os.environ
     os.environ["FLYDSL_RUNTIME_CACHE_DIR"] = _flydsl_cache

+# Always expose aiter.dtypes — it only needs torch + a GFX hint, both of which
+# work on non-ROCm if GPU_ARCHS is set. Keeping it outside the CK/HIP try block
+# means tests that only use dtypes.* can run on CUDA.
+try:
+    from .utility import dtypes as dtypes  # noqa: E402
+except Exception as _e:
+    logger.warning("aiter.dtypes unavailable: %s", _e)
+
 if sys.platform == "win32":
     logger.info("Windows: CK and HIP ops are not available. Triton ops only.")
 elif AITER_AOT_IMPORT:
     from .jit import core as core  # noqa: E402
 else:
     try:
         from .jit import core as core  # noqa: E402
-        from .utility import dtypes as dtypes  # noqa: E402
         from .ops.enum import *  # noqa: F403,E402
